This paper discusses the use of algorithmic systems in various domains, including criminal justice, lending and insurance, and the allocation of public services. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of "Computers and Society" (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper focuses on the fairness of these algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also mentions concerns regarding discrimination and bias, which could place it in the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of prediction algorithms, which could also place it in the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS).
